        "description": "Consider a linear function f(x) = Ax + B. Let's define g^(0)(x) = x and\ng^(n)(x) = f(g^(n-1)(x)) for n > 0. For the given integer values A, B, n and x\nfind the value of g^(n)(x) modulo 10^9 + 7. Input The only line contains four\nintegers A, B, n and x (1 \u2264 A, B, x \u2264 10^9, 1 \u2264 n \u2264 10^18) \u2014 the parameters\nfrom the problem statement. Note that the given value n can be too large, so\nyou should use 64-bit integer type to store it. In C++ you can use the long\nlong integer type and in Java you can use long integer type. Output Print the\nonly integer s \u2014 the value g^(n)(x) modulo 10^9 + 7. Examples Input 3 4 1 1\nOutput 7 Input 3 4 2 1 Output 25 Input 3 4 3 1 Output 79\n\n",
